sentences: From 1921 to 1926, Klohr was a trombonist in Henry Fillmore's concert band.
Klohr died of a heart attack in 1956, and was buried at St. Joseph Cemetery in Cincinnati.

sentences: John Nicholas Klohr (July 27, 1869 – February 17, 1956) was a composer of band music.
He was a member of the Syrian Temple for over 50 years, as well as a member of the Knights of Pythias and the Fraternal Order of Eagles.
